description: Members of A055932 which are not least prime signatures (cf. A025487).
example: 18 = 2*3*3 and all prime divisors are consecutive primes but the least prime signature is 12 = 2*2*3; so a(1) = 18.
author: _Alford Arnold_, Aug 22 2000
extensions: More terms from Larry Reeves (larryr(AT)acm.org), Nov 28 2000
